Day 10: Linux Bash Scripts
The support team needs a script to back up a static website.
Create news_backup.sh to archive /var/www/html/news, store it in /backup/, and copy it to the backup server.

Details:

App Server 2 → stapp02
IP: 172.16.238.11
Hostname: stapp02.stratos.xfusioncorp.com
SSH User: steve
Backup Server→ stbkp01
IP: 172.16.238.16
Hostname: stbkp01.stratos.xfusioncorp.com
SSH User: clint
Solution:

ssh steve@stapp02
sudo yum install -y zip
sudo mkdir -p /scripts
sudo vi /scripts/news_backup.sh
Script content:

#!/bin/bash
zip -r /backup/xfusioncorp_news.zip /var/www/html/news
scp /backup/xfusioncorp_news.zip clint@stbkp01:/backup
Make it executable:

sudo chmod +x /scripts/news_backup.sh
ssh-keygen
ssh-copy-id clint@stbkp01
/scripts/news_backup.sh
Verify:

ssh clint@stbkp01
ls -la /backup/
Result:

-rw-r--r-- 1 clint clint 588 Aug 19 18:06 xfusioncorp_news.zip
The backup archive is successfully created and copied to the backup server.
